{{Infobox person | name = Arthur Heulhard | image = Arthur Heulhard.jpg | birth_date = {{birth date|1849|05|11}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date and age|1920|01|02|1849|05|11}} | death_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Arthur Heulhard''' (May 11, 1849 - January 2, 1920) was a French [[journalist]] and writer, best known as an advocate of the [[Christ myth theory]].
Heulhard was born in [[Lormes]]. He was the author of ''Le Mensonge Chrétien'', a series of eleven volumes declaring [[Jesus]] had no historical existence. According to Heulhard it was [[Barabbas]] who was [[Crucifixion|crucifixed]] by [[Pontius Pilate]] and Christians actually worship Barabbas under the name Jesus, an imaginary person invented by the early [[Christian Church|Church]].<ref>[[Maurice Goguel|Goguel, Maurice]]. (1926). [https://archive.org/stream/jesusthenazarene008778mbp#page/n35/mode/2up/ ''Jesus The Nazarene: Myth Or History?'']. [[D. Appleton & Company]]. Footnote 41. p. 20</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20171031180829/http://radikalkritik.de/geschichte/paul-louis-couchoud "Paul-Louis Couchoud"]. RadikalKritik. Retrieved 30 October 2017. "A man of erudite erudition, Arthur Heulhard, wrote under the title ''The Christian Lie'' a dozen volumes whose essential thesis is that the one crucified by Pilate is Barabbas."</ref> Heulhard gained a follower, the French scholar Daniel Massé who supported his thesis and authored a book on the subject.<ref>[[Paul-Louis Couchoud|Couchoud, P. L]]; Stahl, R. (1927). ''Jesus Barabbas''. ''[[The Hibbert Journal]]'' 25: 26–42.</ref>
He was a member of the Fourchette Harmonique Club of Bibliophiles and wrote for the ''L'art Musical and La France Chorale''.<ref>Ellis, Katharine. (2005). ''Interpreting the Musical Past : Early Music in Nineteenth-Century France: Early Music in Nineteenth-Century France''. [[Oxford University Press]]. p. 259. {{ISBN|978-0-19-536585-6}}</ref>
==Selected publications==
*''Le Mensonge Chrétien: Jésus-Christ n'a pas existé'' (11 volumes, 1908-1910) :Volume I: ''Le Charpentier''. :Volume II: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChrtien-LeRoiDesJuifs-Volume2 ''Le Roi des Juifs'']. :Volume III: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LesMarchandsDeChrist-Volume3 ''Les marchands de Christ'']. :Volume IV: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChrtien-LeSaint-esprit-Volume4 ''Le Saint-Esprit'']. :Volume V: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LeGogotha-Volume5 ''Le Gogotha'']. :Volume VI: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LevangileDeNessus-Volume6 ''L'évangile de Nessus'']. :Volume VII: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LesEvangilesDeSatanI-Volume7 ''Les évangiles de Satan''] (Part 1). :Volume VIII: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LesEvangilesDeSatanIi-Volume8 ''Les évangiles de Satan''] (Part 2). :Volume IX: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LesEvangilesDeSatanIii-Volume9 ''Les évangiles de Satan''] (Part 3). :Volume X: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-Bar-abbas-Volume10 ''Bar-Abbas'']. :Volume XI: [https://archive.org/details/LeMensongeChretien-LeJuifDeRapport-Volume11 ''Le Juif de rapport'']. *''Le Mensonge chrétien. La Vérité: Barabbas - Le Mensonge: Jésus'' (reduced edition in one volume, 1913)
