{{Infobox academic |image = Hienadź Sahanovič, 2017.jpg |caption = Sahanovič in 2017 |birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1961|1|13}} |birth_place = Turnaja, [[Ivatsevichy District]], [[Brest Region]], [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic]] |sub_discipline = History of Eastern Europe |workplaces = {{unbulleted list | [[University of Warsaw]] | [[European Humanities University]]}} |alma_mater = [[Maxim Tank Belarusian State Pedagogical University]] }}
'''Hienadź Sahanovič''' (Генадзь Сагановіч) is a [[Belarus]]ian historian. He specializes in the early modern period of Central European and Belarusian history.
== Education and academic career ==
In 1984 Sahanovič graduated from the [[Maxim Tank Belarusian State Pedagogical University]] in [[Minsk|Miensk]]. Beginning in 1986 he became an active member of the democratic oppostion in Soviet Belarus.<ref>«Бабілён» http://www.slounik.org/153727.html</ref> In 1989 Sahanovič obtained a PhD degree in history from the Institute of History, [[National Academy of Sciences of Belarus]], where he worked as a researcher between 1984 and 2005. His employment was terminated,<ref>Arkadź Šanski. 2005. Sahanovič zvolnieny [Sahanovič was Fired {from the Institute of History}]. ''Naša niva'', July 1. https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=100176</ref> in the course of the politically-motivated purge of historians and social scientists, whose research did not follow the government's official line.<ref>The cause of Sahanovič's dismissal was the fact that during his leisure he went to do archival research in Cracow. Officially, the institute maintains that the historian was dismissed, because he published an article on the state of Belarusian historiography in the Russian periodical ''Rodina''. (See: Sahanoviču pahražajuć zvalnieńniem [Sahanovič Threatened with Dismissal]. 2005. ''Naša niva'', April 26. https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=100133). After 2003 many leading Belarusian historians were dismissed from the Belarusian Academy of Sciences and the country's universities in order to reformulate the officially espoused vision of Belarusian history by making it more pro-Russian. (See: Hienadź Kanstancinaŭ. 2008. Prastora i identyčnasć u Bielarusi [Space and Identity in Belarus]. ''DW''. November 16. https://www.dw.com/ru/прастора-і-ідэнтычнасць-у-беларусі/a-3797674 ; Hienadź Sahanovič. 2008. Vajna z bielaruskaj historyjaj [The War Against Belarusian History]. ''Žyvie Bielaruś''. October 15. http://jivebelarus.net/society/war-against-belarusian-history.html)</ref> Sahanovič moved to the [[European Humanities University]] (EHU), then still based in the Belarusian capital of Miensk.<ref> Саганович, Геннадий Николаевич (кандидат исторических наук ; род. 1961) http://unicat.nlb.by/scient/pls/dict.prn_ref?tu=e&tq=v0&name_view=va_all&a001=BY-NLB-ar91367&strq=l_siz=10</ref> The EHU ceased operating in Belarus in 2004.<ref>Ash, Lucy. 2013. Belarus's University in Exile. ''BBC News''. www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-22254545</ref>
In 1994 Sahanovič founded the journal ''Belaruski Histaryčny Ahliad/Belarusian Historical Review'', and since then has served as its Editor-in-Chief.<ref>Belaruskì Gìstaryčny Aglâd = Belarusian Historical Review: [navukovy časopìs / red. Genadz' Saganovìč] http://alpha.bn.org.pl/search~S5*pol?/asahanowicz/asahanowicz/1%2C1%2C25%2CB/frameset&FF=asahanowicz+hienadz~a+++++1961&3%2C%2C25 ; ''Belarusian Historical Review'' http://bha.knihi.com/index-e.htm</ref>. At the same time, he was also a member of the editorial board of another new learned journal (established in 1993), devoted to Belarusian studies, namely, ''Беларусіка Belarusika/Albaruthenica'', as founded and edited by the leading Belarusian philologist and historian Adam Maldzis (Адам Мальдзіс).<ref>Belarusìka = Albaruthenica. Kn. 1 / [rèd. Adam Mal'dzìs, Genadz' Saganovič, Genadz' Cychun] ; Mìžnarodnaja asacyjacyja belarusìstaǔ, Nacyjanal'ny navukova-asvetny cèntr ìmja Francìška Skaryny. http://alpha.bn.org.pl/search~S5*pol?/asahanowicz/asahanowicz/1%2C1%2C25%2CB/frameset&FF=asahanowicz+hienadz~a+++++1961&2%2C%2C25</ref>
Sahanovič works and does research at the EHU, Vilnius, Lithuania,<ref>EHU: Staff: Henadz Sahanovich http://en.ehu.lt/staff/henadz-sahanovich/</ref> and at the [[University of Warsaw]] in the Center for Belarusian Studies, Center for East European Studies.<ref>Centrum Studiów Białoruskich przy SEW UW, http://studium.uw.edu.pl/struktura/centrum-studiow-bialoruskich-przy-sew-uw/</ref> In 2018 Sahanovič obtained a [[Habilitation]] degree in history from the University of Warsaw.<ref>Генадзь Сагановіч абараніў доктарскую http://nn.by/?c=ar&i=210577</ref>
==Awards==
For his research Sahanovič received a Belarusian PEN Club’s [[Francišak Bahuševič]] award in 1995,<ref> Саганович, Геннадий Николаевич (кандидат исторических наук ; род. 1961) http://unicat.nlb.by/scient/pls/dict.prn_ref?tu=e&tq=v0&name_view=va_all&a001=BY-NLB-ar91367&strq=l_siz=10 ; ЛЯЎРЭАТАМ ПРЭМІІ ІМЯ ФРАНЦІШКА БАГУШЭВІЧА СТАЎ ГІСТОРЫК ЗАХАР ШЫБЕКА http://www.svaboda.org/a/24852684.html</ref> and six years later, in 2001, an award conferred by the Polish journal ''Przegląd Wschodni''.<ref>Laureaci nagrody „Przeglądu Wschodniego” 1993–2013 http://studium.uw.edu.pl/wp-content/uploads/2018/.../Laureaci-starzy.pdf</ref>
